org.forgerock.openam.sm.datalayer.api

Interface QueueConfiguration

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    CTSQueueConfiguration

    public interface QueueConfiguration
    Interface describing the configuration for asynchronous processing queues.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      int getProcessors()
      The number of asynchronous Task Processors that should be initialised.
      int getQueueSize()
      The size of each work queue that is used by the asynchronous work queue mechanism.
      int getQueueTimeout()
      The maximum duration the caller should wait to place their asynchronous task on a work queue, and the maximum duration the caller should wait to retrieve the result of processing from the queue.

    • Method Detail

      • getQueueTimeout

        int getQueueTimeout()
        The maximum duration the caller should wait to place their asynchronous task on a work queue, and the maximum duration the caller should wait to retrieve the result of processing from the queue.
        Returns:
        A positive integer in seconds to wait.

      • getQueueSize

        int getQueueSize()
        The size of each work queue that is used by the asynchronous work queue mechanism. This will control how many items can be queued up in the CTS before this causes the caller to block.
        Returns:
        A positive integer for the size of the queue,

      • getProcessors

        int getProcessors()
           throws DataLayerException
        The number of asynchronous Task Processors that should be initialised. This value is based on the number of connections available.
        Returns:
        A positive number of processors to initialise.
        Throws:
        DataLayerException - If there was any issue resolving the configuration of the processors.
        See Also:
        ConnectionConfigFactory, QueueSelector
